FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773027579
OL,3,CGender-affirming hormone treatment for
OL,4,Cchildren halted by NHS
OL,6,FTaking such hormones can cause
OL,7,Firreversible changes, such as breast
OL,8,Fdevelopment when taking oestrogen, or
OL,9,Fdeepening of the voice caused by
OL,10,Ftaking testosterone.
OL,12,FIn the 2024 Cass Review into
OL,13,Fchildren's gender care, Baroness
OL,14,FHilary Cass recommended "extreme
OL,15,Fcaution" in providing such treatment,
OL,16,Fand a "clear clinical rationale for
OL,17,Fproviding hormones at this stage
OL,18,Frather than waiting until an
OL,19,Findividual reaches 18".
OL,26,@vD@YOUwD@HO]xD@GOU{D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1773027579
OL,3,CGender-affirming hormone treatment for
OL,4,Cchildren halted by NHS
OL,6,FA review by NHS England has since
OL,7,Ffound that the evidence is too weak to
OL,8,Fshow whether such treatment is either
OL,9,Fbeneficial or harmful to children with
OL,10,Fgender dysphoria.
OL,12,FIt is understood the NHS is continuing
OL,13,Fto examine evidence for masculinising
OL,14,Fand feminising hormones for adults.
OL,16,FNHS England said 16 and 17-year-old
OL,17,Fpatients currently receiving cross-sex
OL,18,Fhormones can continue to receive
OL,19,Ftreatment but it must be reviewed
OL,20,Findividually with clinicians.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
